						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Śiṟu-Tirukkōyil-Bhaṭāraka at Uṟumūr, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> village of Na[l*]vayalūr-kūṟṟam on the north bank of the river, by Āridaṉ Kaṇṇaṉ a resident of the village. The gift was left in charge of the local assembly. </p>						

						</summary>
